For example, to set a maximum episode length of 200 timesteps, you can use the following code:
```
tune.run(
    "PPO",
    stop={
        "episode_reward_mean": 200,
    },
    config={
        "evaluation_duration": 200,
        "evaluation_duration_unit": "timesteps",
    },
)
```
This will run the PPO algorithm for up to 200 timesteps per evaluation, and will stop the training process when the mean episode reward reaches 200.

Alternatively, you can use the `evaluation_duration` parameter to set a maximum duration for the training process, regardless of the number of episodes. For example:
```
tune.run(
    "PPO",
    stop={
        "episode_reward_mean": 200,
    },
    config={
        "evaluation_duration": 3600,  # 1 hour
    },
)
```
This will run the PPO algorithm for up to 1 hour, and will stop the training process when the mean episode reward reaches 200.

Note that the `evaluation_duration` parameter is only used for the evaluation phase of the training process, and does not affect the training phase.

